******
[1] India (Himachal Pradesh, Uttar Pradesh, Haryana)
Date: Wed 30 Mar 2011
Source: IBN Live, Press Trust of India (PTI) report [edited]
http://ibnlive.in.com/generalnewsfeed/news/fungal-disease-infects-wheat-crop-in-lower-areas-of-himachal/630261.html


Fungal disease infects wheat crop in lower areas of Himachal
------------------------------------------------------------
Wheat crop in large areas in the lower hills of Himachal Pradesh have
been severely infected by a fungal disease, chief minister Prem Kumar
Dhumal told the Assembly. "Yellow rust has hit the wheat crop and its
acute effect had been seen in more than 16 941 hectares [about 42 000
acres]," he said.

"The disease also severely affected the wheat crop in the northern
states of Punjab [ProMED-mail post 20110211.0469], Haryana, and Uttar
Pradesh," Dhumal said.

A congress member said that 60 per cent of wheat crop has been
damaged in the state [of Himachal Pradesh] and blamed the government
for supplying substandard seeds.

