******
[2] India (Jammu and Kashmir)
Date: Wed 9 Mar 2011
Source: New Tang Dynasty (NTD) Television [edited]
http://english.ntdtv.com/ntdtv_en/news_asia/2011-03-09/yellow-rust-disease-destroys-wheat-crop-in-northern-india.html


Yellow rust destroys wheat crop in northern India
-------------------------------------------------
A wheat disease called yellow rust has destroyed about 60 per cent of
wheat plantations in Kathua, located in India's northern Jammu and
Kashmir state.

Farmers are worried about the situation, as most of them cannot
afford pesticides. They say the government should be of more
assistance. More than 24 000 acres [about 9700 ha] of wheat are
affected by yellow rust, and farmers are facing huge losses.

However, the district agriculture department says it is taking steps
to control the situation. The officials blamed heavy, unseasonal rains
for the disease.

--
